            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20midst%20of%20the%20terrible%20ordeals%20of%20life%2C%20we%20often%20don't%20know%20to%20whom%20we%20can%20turn.%20In%202%20Kings%2020%2C%20Hezekiah%20was%20facing%20death%20because%20a%20terrible%20sickness%20had%20attacked%20his%20body.%20To%20whom%20did%20he%20turn%20in%20his%20hour%20of%20need%3F%20The%20Word%20of%20God%20tells%20us%20that%20%22he%20turned%20his%20face%20to%20the%20wall%20and%20prayed%20to%20the%20Lord%22%20(v.%202).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20%22wall%22%20represents%20the%20tower%20of%20the%20Lord.%20In%20his%20moment%20of%20desperate%20need%2C%20Hezekiah's%20eyes%20were%20no%20longer%20fixed%20on%20human%20methods%20and%20reports.%20The%20things%20of%20the%20world%20no%20longer%20distracted%20his%20vision.%20Rather%2C%20he%20raced%20to%20safety%20inside%20the%20tower%20of%20the%20Lord.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20Lord%20heard%20his%20cry%20and%20instructed%20Isaiah%20to%20have%20Hezekiah's%20servants%20apply%20an%20ointment%20made%20from%20figs.%20They%20obeyed%20his%20command%2C%20and%20Hezekiah%20was%20healed.%20Because%20he%20had%20run%20to%20God%2C%20God%20heard%20his%20prayer%2C%20saw%20his%20tears%2C%20and%20added%20fifteen%20years%20to%20his%20life%20(vv.%205-6).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20tower%20of%20the%20Lord%20is%20a%20supernatural%20tower.%20It%20is%20so%20strong%20that%20it%20can%20turn%20the%20sun%20backward%20ten%20degrees%2C%20a%20feat%20that%20boggles%20the%20mind%20when%20the%20laws%20of%20physics%20are%20considered.%20Leave%20your%20present%20fears%20behind%20and%20run%20into%20the%20tower%20of%20the%20Lord.%20It%20is%20the%20one%20place%20you%20are%20safe!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
            "id": "ot-passage",
