            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "2Kgs.20:1-22:2",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3E2%20Kings%2020%3A1-22%3A2%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_20_1%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E2%20Kings%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EHezekiah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Sickness%20and%20Recovery%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EAbout%20that%20time%20Hezekiah%20became%20deathly%20ill%2C%20and%20the%20prophet%20Isaiah%20son%20of%20Amoz%20went%20to%20visit%20him.%20He%20gave%20the%20king%20this%20message%3A%20%26%23x201C%3BThis%20is%20what%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20says%3A%20Set%20your%20affairs%20in%20order%2C%20for%20you%20are%20going%20to%20die.%20You%20will%20not%20recover%20from%20this%20illness.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_20_2%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20Hezekiah%20heard%20this%2C%20he%20turned%20his%20face%20to%20the%20wall%20and%20prayed%20to%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_20_3%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BRemember%2C%20O%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20how%20I%20have%20always%20been%20faithful%20to%20you%20and%20have%20served%20you%20single-mindedly%2C%20always%20doing%20what%20pleases%20you.%26%23x201D%3B%20Then%20he%20broke%20down%20and%20wept%20bitterly.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_20_4%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20before%20Isaiah%20had%20left%20the%20middle%20courtyard%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E20%3A4%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20Greek%20version%20and%20an%20alternate%20reading%20in%20the%20Masoretic%20Text%3B%20the%20other%20alternate%20reads%20%3Cem%3Ethe%20middle%20of%20the%20city.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20this%20message%20came%20to%20him%20from%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%3A%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_20_5%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BGo%20back%20to%20Hezekiah%2C%20the%20leader%20of%20my%20people.%20Tell%20him%2C%20%26%23x2018%3BThis%20is%20what%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20the%20God%20of%20your%20ancestor%20David%2C%20says%3A%20I%20have%20heard%20your%20prayer%20and%20seen%20your%20tears.%20I%20will%20heal%20you%2C%20and%20three%20days%20from%20now%20you%20will%20get%20out%20of%20bed%20and%20go%20to%20the%20Temple%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_20_6%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EI%20will%20add%20fifteen%20years%20to%20your%20life%2C%20and%20I%20will%20rescue%20you%20and%20this%20city%20from%20the%20king%20of%20Assyria.%20I%20will%20defend%20this%20city%20for%20my%20own%20honor%20and%20for%20the%20sake%20of%20my%20servant%20David.%26%23x2019%3B%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_20_7%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Isaiah%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BMake%20an%20ointment%20from%20figs.%26%23x201D%3B%20So%20Hezekiah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20servants%20spread%20the%20ointment%20over%20the%20boil%2C%20and%20Hezekiah%20recovered!%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_20_8%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Hezekiah%20had%20said%20to%20Isaiah%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BWhat%20sign%20will%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20give%20to%20prove%20that%20he%20will%20heal%20me%20and%20that%20I%20will%20go%20to%20the%20Temple%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20three%20days%20from%20now%3F%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_20_9%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EIsaiah%20replied%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BThis%20is%20the%20sign%20from%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20to%20prove%20that%20he%20will%20do%20as%20he%20promised.%20Would%20you%20like%20the%20shadow%20on%20the%20sundial%20to%20go%20forward%20ten%20steps%20or%20backward%20ten%20steps%3F%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E20%3A9%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3EThe%20shadow%20on%20the%20sundial%20has%20gone%20forward%20ten%20steps%3B%20do%20you%20want%20it%20to%20go%20backward%20ten%20steps%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_20_10%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BThe%20shadow%20always%20moves%20forward%2C%26%23x201D%3B%20Hezekiah%20replied%2C%20%26%23x201C%3Bso%20that%20would%20be%20easy.%20Make%20it%20go%20ten%20steps%20backward%20instead.%26%23x201D%3B%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_20_11%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20Isaiah%20the%20prophet%20asked%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20to%20do%20this%2C%20and%20he%20caused%20the%20shadow%20to%20move%20ten%20steps%20backward%20on%20the%20sundial%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E20%3A11%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Ethe%20steps.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20of%20Ahaz!%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_20_12%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EEnvoys%20from%20Babylon%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3ESoon%20after%20this%2C%20Merodach-baladan%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E20%3A12%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20some%20Hebrew%20manuscripts%20and%20Greek%20and%20Syriac%20versions%20(see%20also%20Isa%2039%3A1)%3B%20Masoretic%20Text%20reads%20%3Cem%3EBerodach-baladan.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20son%20of%20Baladan%2C%20king%20of%20Babylon%2C%20sent%20Hezekiah%20his%20best%20wishes%20and%20a%20gift%2C%20for%20he%20had%20heard%20that%20Hezekiah%20had%20been%20very%20sick.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_20_13%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3EHezekiah%20received%20the%20Babylonian%20envoys%20and%20showed%20them%20everything%20in%20his%20treasure-houses%26%23x2014%3Bthe%20silver%2C%20the%20gold%2C%20the%20spices%2C%20and%20the%20aromatic%20oils.%20He%20also%20took%20them%20to%20see%20his%20armory%20and%20showed%20them%20everything%20in%20his%20royal%20treasuries!%20There%20was%20nothing%20in%20his%20palace%20or%20kingdom%20that%20Hezekiah%20did%20not%20show%20them.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_20_14%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Isaiah%20the%20prophet%20went%20to%20King%20Hezekiah%20and%20asked%20him%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BWhat%20did%20those%20men%20want%3F%20Where%20were%20they%20from%3F%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3EHezekiah%20replied%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BThey%20came%20from%20the%20distant%20land%20of%20Babylon.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_20_15%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BWhat%20did%20they%20see%20in%20your%20palace%3F%26%23x201D%3B%20Isaiah%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%26%23x201C%3BThey%20saw%20everything%2C%26%23x201D%3B%20Hezekiah%20replied.%20%26%23x201C%3BI%20showed%20them%20everything%20I%20own%26%23x2014%3Ball%20my%20royal%20treasuries.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_20_16%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Isaiah%20said%20to%20Hezekiah%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BListen%20to%20this%20message%20from%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%3A%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_20_17%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20time%20is%20coming%20when%20everything%20in%20your%20palace%26%23x2014%3Ball%20the%20treasures%20stored%20up%20by%20your%20ancestors%20until%20now%26%23x2014%3Bwill%20be%20carried%20off%20to%20Babylon.%20Nothing%20will%20be%20left%2C%20says%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_20_18%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3ESome%20of%20your%20very%20own%20sons%20will%20be%20taken%20away%20into%20exile.%20They%20will%20become%20eunuchs%20who%20will%20serve%20in%20the%20palace%20of%20Babylon%26%23x2019%3Bs%20king.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_20_19%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%2219%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Hezekiah%20said%20to%20Isaiah%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BThis%20message%20you%20have%20given%20me%20from%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20is%20good.%26%23x201D%3B%20For%20the%20king%20was%20thinking%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BAt%20least%20there%20will%20be%20peace%20and%20security%20during%20my%20lifetime.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_20_20%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%2220%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E20%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20rest%20of%20the%20events%20in%20Hezekiah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20reign%2C%20including%20the%20extent%20of%20his%20power%20and%20how%20he%20built%20a%20pool%20and%20dug%20a%20tunnel%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E20%3A20%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Ewatercourse.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20to%20bring%20water%20into%20the%20city%2C%20are%20recorded%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Book%20of%20the%20History%20of%20the%20Kings%20of%20Judah.%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_20_21%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%2221%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E21%3C%2Fspan%3EHezekiah%20died%2C%20and%20his%20son%20Manasseh%20became%20the%20next%20king.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_21_1%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2221%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E2%20Kings%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E21%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EManasseh%20Rules%20in%20Judah%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EManasseh%20was%20twelve%20years%20old%20when%20he%20became%20king%2C%20and%20he%20reigned%20in%20Jerusalem%20fifty-five%20years.%20His%20mother%20was%20Hephzibah.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_21_2%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2221%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20did%20what%20was%20evil%20in%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20sight%2C%20following%20the%20detestable%20practices%20of%20the%20pagan%20nations%20that%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20had%20driven%20from%20the%20land%20ahead%20of%20the%20Israelites.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_21_3%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2221%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20rebuilt%20the%20pagan%20shrines%20his%20father%2C%20Hezekiah%2C%20had%20destroyed.%20He%20constructed%20altars%20for%20Baal%20and%20set%20up%20an%20Asherah%20pole%2C%20just%20as%20King%20Ahab%20of%20Israel%20had%20done.%20He%20also%20bowed%20before%20all%20the%20powers%20of%20the%20heavens%20and%20worshiped%20them.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_21_4%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2221%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20built%20pagan%20altars%20in%20the%20Temple%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20the%20place%20where%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20had%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BMy%20name%20will%20remain%20in%20Jerusalem%20forever.%26%23x201D%3B%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_21_5%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2221%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20built%20these%20altars%20for%20all%20the%20powers%20of%20the%20heavens%20in%20both%20courtyards%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Temple.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_21_6%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2221%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EManasseh%20also%20sacrificed%20his%20own%20son%20in%20the%20fire.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E21%3A6%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3Ealso%20made%20his%20son%20pass%20through%20the%20fire.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20He%20practiced%20sorcery%20and%20divination%2C%20and%20he%20consulted%20with%20mediums%20and%20psychics.%20He%20did%20much%20that%20was%20evil%20in%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20sight%2C%20arousing%20his%20anger.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_21_7%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2221%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EManasseh%20even%20made%20a%20carved%20image%20of%20Asherah%20and%20set%20it%20up%20in%20the%20Temple%2C%20the%20very%20place%20where%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20had%20told%20David%20and%20his%20son%20Solomon%3A%20%26%23x201C%3BMy%20name%20will%20be%20honored%20forever%20in%20this%20Temple%20and%20in%20Jerusalem%26%23x2014%3Bthe%20city%20I%20have%20chosen%20from%20among%20all%20the%20tribes%20of%20Israel.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_21_8%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2221%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EIf%20the%20Israelites%20will%20be%20careful%20to%20obey%20my%20commands%26%23x2014%3Ball%20the%20laws%20my%20servant%20Moses%20gave%20them%26%23x2014%3BI%20will%20not%20send%20them%20into%20exile%20from%20this%20land%20that%20I%20gave%20their%20ancestors.%26%23x201D%3B%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_21_9%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2221%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20the%20people%20refused%20to%20listen%2C%20and%20Manasseh%20led%20them%20to%20do%20even%20more%20evil%20than%20the%20pagan%20nations%20that%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20had%20destroyed%20when%20the%20people%20of%20Israel%20entered%20the%20land.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_21_10%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2221%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20said%20through%20his%20servants%20the%20prophets%3A%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_21_11%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2221%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BKing%20Manasseh%20of%20Judah%20has%20done%20many%20detestable%20things.%20He%20is%20even%20more%20wicked%20than%20the%20Amorites%2C%20who%20lived%20in%20this%20land%20before%20Israel.%20He%20has%20caused%20the%20people%20of%20Judah%20to%20sin%20with%20his%20idols.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E21%3A11%3C%2Fspan%3E%20The%20Hebrew%20term%20(literally%20%3Cem%3Eround%20things%3C%2Fem%3E)%20probably%20alludes%20to%20dung%3B%20also%20in%2021%3A21.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_21_12%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2221%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20this%20is%20what%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20the%20God%20of%20Israel%2C%20says%3A%20I%20will%20bring%20such%20disaster%20on%20Jerusalem%20and%20Judah%20that%20the%20ears%20of%20those%20who%20hear%20about%20it%20will%20tingle%20with%20horror.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_21_13%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2221%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3EI%20will%20judge%20Jerusalem%20by%20the%20same%20standard%20I%20used%20for%20Samaria%20and%20the%20same%20measure%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%